play with my food.

25:05.580 --> 25:07.210
This is Auntie Regina.

25:08.540 --> 25:11.710
Are we putting up the gutters
or eating the gutters?

25:11.710 --> 25:13.830
I'm just cutting it
to size, Mom.

25:13.830 --> 25:17.380
♪ Colored lights
and candy canes ♪

25:17.380 --> 25:18.170
Mmm.

25:18.170 --> 25:21.290
Practical and delicious.

25:23.540 --> 25:26.080
♪ A crackling fire
calls out your name ♪

25:26.080 --> 25:28.330
It's really hard
getting older.

25:28.330 --> 25:30.500
It is.

25:30.500 --> 25:33.500
What do you find hard?

25:33.500 --> 25:37.120
I don't like that
my boots don't fit anymore.

25:37.120 --> 25:40.120
And it's not just that.

25:40.120 --> 25:42.380
There's so many
changes happening.

25:42.380 --> 25:43.920
♪ Close to the one
I love the most ♪

25:43.920 --> 25:45.460
There are.

25:45.460 --> 25:47.330
They can be tough.

25:47.330 --> 25:49.380
♪ Holly hung with mistletoe ♪

25:49.380 --> 25:51.920
You have any ideas
what we should do about it?

25:51.920 --> 25:54.290
♪ Silver packages
with bright red bows ♪

25:54.290 --> 25:56.120
Maybe we should
ask Santa.

25:56.120 --> 25:57.880
♪ Ask the children,
they all know ♪

25:57.880 --> 26:00.250
I think
that's a great idea.

26:02.540 --> 26:05.750
This one is way too long.

26:09.210 --> 26:11.170
Hey.

26:11.170 --> 26:13.960
It's gonna be okay.
Mm-hmm.

26:13.960 --> 26:16.250
Thanks for being here
with me.

26:16.250 --> 26:17.960
Of course.

26:18.830 --> 26:22.500
Mm.

26:22.500 --> 26:23.750
What?

26:23.750 --> 26:26.880
It's just, um...

26:26.880 --> 26:29.830
When Theo was born,

26:29.830 --> 26:31.830
with my drinking,

26:31.830 --> 26:33.580
I wasn't there.

26:33.580 --> 26:39.250
So as crazy
as this situation is,

26:39.250 --> 26:41.710
I get a chance to do what
I didn't do the first time.

26:43.670 --> 26:46.710
Hello. I'm Dr. Ehrlich.

26:46.710 --> 26:49.500
So, you fell on the ice
and had some spotting.

26:49.500 --> 26:50.500
I did, yes.

26:50.500 --> 26:51.580
How far along are you?

26:51.580 --> 26:53.290
14 weeks.

26:53.290 --> 26:55.500
If you want
to lay back there,

26:55.500 --> 26:56.620
let's see
how your baby's doing.

26:56.620 --> 26:57.420
Okay.

26:57.420 --> 26:58.460
I'm gonna be outside.

26:58.460 --> 27:00.210
No. Stay.

27:01.620 --> 27:04.620
You're the father.
You need to be here.

27:07.960 --> 27:10.620
You were such
a great dad today.

27:12.420 --> 27:14.380
I just want everybody
to be okay.

27:18.880 --> 27:20.380
I think my --

27:20.380 --> 27:22.080
I think my favorite was, uh,

27:22.080 --> 27:24.040
"I don't want to spend
the year I have left

27:24.040 --> 27:25.580
standing in line
behind you."

27:26.380 --> 27:27.880
Mmm. Delicious.

27:27.880 --> 27:29.540
Here.

27:29.540 --> 27:31.210
Mmm, mmm.

27:33.290 --> 27:36.380
Look at us
bonding over cancer.

27:36.380 --> 27:37.540
It's a nice change.

27:43.040 --> 27:47.790
So...friends?

27:47.790 --> 27:50.040
Yeah. I can do friends.

27:50.040 --> 27:51.380
I don't think
you can do friends.

27:51.380 --> 27:52.420
I have tons of friends.
Yeah.

27:52.420 --> 27:53.460
I'm stupid with friends.

27:53.460 --> 27:54.620
No, I'm talking about
female friends.

27:54.620 --> 27:56.170
I have female friends.

27:56.170 --> 27:57.290
No,
I'm talking about women

27:57.290 --> 27:58.790
who are
not just your friends

27:58.790 --> 28:01.500
because they are the spouses
of your guy friends.

28:03.710 --> 28:04.710
Just eat your brittle.

28:04.710 --> 28:06.710
Oh.

28:06.710 --> 28:09.420
And keep it in the tin.
Come on, this is a new car.

28:09.420 --> 28:10.540
Calm down.

28:10.540 --> 28:12.040
The only thing better
than new-car smell

28:12.040 --> 28:13.960
is peanut brittle smell.

28:13.960 --> 28:16.170
Wow. What is --

28:16.170 --> 28:18.670
What have we here?

28:18.670 --> 28:21.540
Is this a --
another one of your friends

28:21.540 --> 28:22.960
who you cannot
be friends with?

28:22.960 --> 28:24.750
Screw it.

28:24.750 --> 28:26.830
If we're gonna be friends,
I can tell anything, right?

28:26.830 --> 28:30.040
Yeah.
Okay, great.

28:30.040 --> 28:32.420
You remember,
uh, my neighbor

28:32.420 --> 28:34.460
who accused me
of stealing her paper?

28:34.460 --> 28:38.080
Mrs. Goldfeine,
the old lady with a walker?

28:38.080 --> 28:40.460
Well, she wore me down.

28:40.460 --> 28:42.670
She wore me down,
and she broke my heart,

28:42.670 --> 28:44.670
and I broke her hip.

28:47.290 --> 28:48.920
We did it
right where you're sitting.

28:48.920 --> 28:50.420
Oh, great.

28:50.420 --> 28:51.670
And it took me
an hour and a half

28:51.670 --> 28:52.670
to get her
out of the car.

28:52.670 --> 28:56.250
Well, thank you,
Mrs. Goldfeine,

28:56.250 --> 28:57.830
'cause this scarf
is mine now.

28:57.830 --> 28:59.580
Okay. Good news.

28:59.580 --> 29:02.290
The amniotic sac
has not been compromised,

29:02.290 --> 29:04.250
so your baby's fine.
-Okay.

29:04.250 --> 29:06.080
Uh, maybe just take it easy
for the next couple of days --

29:06.080 --> 29:07.380
you know, avoid stress.

29:07.380 --> 29:10.880
It's a holiday,
so that should be easy, right?

29:10.880 --> 29:12.040
Right.

29:12.040 --> 29:14.540
Okay. I'll send the nurse in
to sign you out.

29:14.540 --> 29:15.620
Thank you, Doctor.

29:20.170 --> 29:21.960
What'd I tell you, huh?
Everything's fine.

29:23.000 --> 29:24.290
Um, excuse me.

29:24.290 --> 29:26.210
I'm looking for my mom,
Delilah Dixon.

29:26.210 --> 29:28.920
Oh, yeah.
Your mom is in Room 4.

29:28.920 --> 29:30.170
She's fine.

29:30.170 --> 29:32.210
And the baby
is perfectly healthy.

29:32.210 --> 29:33.960
Go see her.
Go see your mom.

29:43.330 --> 29:46.420
Mom. Oh, my God.
I was so worried.

29:46.420 --> 29:48.120
Sophie, w-what
are you doing here?

29:48.120 --> 29:52.380
I -- I saw on my phone
that you were here, and...

29:52.380 --> 29:53.790
You're pregnant?

29:56.380 --> 29:58.460
Why didn't you tell me?

29:58.460 --> 30:00.120
I was gonna tell you.

30:00.120 --> 30:02.710
I...I was just trying
to find the right time,

30:02.710 --> 30:03.540
and -- and I wasn't --

30:05.620 --> 30:08.000
I wasn't sure
how you'd react.

30:10.960 --> 30:14.170
I mean, are you kidding?

30:14.170 --> 30:16.880
It's great.

30:16.880 --> 30:20.080
And if it's a boy,
then we should name him Jon.

30:23.000 --> 30:24.790
That's a great idea.

30:41.790 --> 30:43.750
Oh, Mom, can we tell
Danny the good news?

30:43.750 --> 30:45.170
Yes, of course.

30:53.330 --> 30:55.750
I'm sorry.

30:55.750 --> 30:58.290
I just -- I can't afford
to have her hate me right now.

30:58.290 --> 30:59.500
She just lost her dad.

30:59.500 --> 31:01.920
Maybe when she's 20,
she can hate me then,

31:01.920 --> 31:03.040
but right now, I just --

31:03.040 --> 31:04.670
You did the right thing.

31:08.420 --> 31:10.120
You should be there
when she tells Danny.

31:21.790 --> 31:25.250
♪ Deck the halls
with boughs of holly ♪

31:25.250 --> 31:27.830
♪ Fa-la-la-la-la,
la-la-la-la ♪
Are you eating
the patio furniture?

31:27.830 --> 31:29.710
Maybe?

31:29.710 --> 31:32.500
♪ 'Tis the season to be jolly ♪
You just brushed your teeth.

31:32.500 --> 31:33.670
Let me get you
a graham cracker,

31:33.670 --> 31:35.420
something that's not
part of the foundation.

31:36.790 --> 31:38.210
♪ Don we now our gay apparel ♪

31:38.210 --> 31:40.290
Hello?

31:40.290 --> 31:41.880
♪ Fa-la-la-la-la,
la-la-la-la ♪
Oh.

31:41.880 --> 31:45.170
How did you get my number?

31:45.170 --> 31:47.540
♪ Troll the ancient
Yule-tide carol ♪
Oh, wow.

31:47.540 --> 31:49.210
No, Theo's right here.

31:49.210 --> 31:50.540
Who is it?

31:52.580 --> 31:53.420
Santa Claus.

31:54.790 --> 31:57.580
Uh...N-No. Sure, Santa.

31:57.580 --> 31:58.880
He's been thinking about it.

31:58.880 --> 32:01.210
He would like
a pair of boots

32:01.210 --> 32:03.170
just like the ones
Superman would wear.

32:03.170 --> 32:04.040
Only rainproof.

32:04.040 --> 32:05.380
Only rainproof.

32:05.380 --> 32:07.880
Okay. Thanks.

32:07.880 --> 32:09.420
Tell him to say hi
to Rudolph for us.

32:09.420 --> 32:11.210
Say hi to Rudolph for us.

32:13.580 --> 32:16.080
And one more thing.

32:16.080 --> 32:18.250
W-What is it, Santa?

32:18.250 --> 32:20.380
When you were
pregnant with Theo,

32:20.380 --> 32:22.170
I could've been better.

32:26.580 --> 32:29.040
Katie, I'll never forgive myself
for not being there.

32:31.170 --> 32:32.920
Thanks for
saying that, Santa.

32:34.750 --> 32:36.170
Okay, Danny.

32:36.170 --> 32:37.420
I think that's as good
as it's gonna get.

32:37.420 --> 32:38.290
-That is nice.
-Whoo.

32:38.290 --> 32:40.330
All right.
I think she's ready.

32:40.330 --> 32:41.540
All right, people.

32:41.540 --> 32:42.880
Let's light this bad boy up.

32:42.880 --> 32:43.960
Bam!

32:52.000 --> 32:55.500
All right, well,
Jon usually made a speech,

32:55.500 --> 32:58.790
even though it's not really
my thing, but, um...

32:58.790 --> 33:02.790
I just wanted to say
thank you all for today

33:02.790 --> 33:04.750
and for every other day.

33:04.750 --> 33:08.080
Danny, Sophie, and I are
really lucky to have all of you.

33:08.080 --> 33:11.500
And this little -- this little
nugget is lucky, too.

33:11.500 --> 33:13.830
-Aww.

33:13.830 --> 33:15.250
But where is Sophie?

33:15.250 --> 33:18.670
Ho, ho, holy cow,
it's Christmas!

33:18.670 --> 33:21.580
-Oh, my goodness.
-Holy cow.

33:21.580 --> 33:23.210
Regina: Wow.

33:23.210 --> 33:25.170
Edward, are you ready?

33:25.170 --> 33:26.670
Ready for what, Santa?

33:26.670 --> 33:29.040
Oh, this?

33:29.040 --> 33:29.920
Hey, everyone.

33:29.920 --> 33:32.040
Well, as you all know,

33:32.040 --> 33:34.210
I take off
tomorrow morning,

33:34.210 --> 33:36.460
and before I head out,

33:36.460 --> 33:39.000
Santa and I
would like to play you

33:39.000 --> 33:40.960
a Yuletide
private concert.

33:40.960 --> 33:41.880
What do you say?
-Oh, yeah!

33:41.880 --> 33:43.420
-Whoo!
-Bring it!

33:43.420 --> 33:44.420
Santa, you ready?

33:44.420 --> 33:46.210
A 1, 2...

33:47.580 --> 33:50.000
Both: ♪ Rockin' around
